    <h2><a class="exception-link" href="#h2-3">The Final Word on Fonts</a></h2>
    <p><a class="exception-link" href="#p-9">Typography is not just about letters; it’s about personality, readability, and making sure your audience doesn’t suffer an eye strain-induced meltdown. Choose wisely, space generously, and for the love of all things legible, never, ever use Papyrus.</a></p>

    <p><a class="exception-link" href="#p-10">And if all else fails, just use Helvetica. No one ever got fired for using Helvetica.</a></p>

